		<p>Given in this budget they also pointed out they are going to increase their capital ratio by 1% by 2016, this does not bode well for depositors. As I understand it, in order to increase the ratio, they have to reduce tier 2 &amp; 3 capital as they increase tier 1 capital (equity capital and disclosed reserves&#8230;i.e real estate, cash, bonds). Problem is, the Tier 1 pool is shrinking as they must be rated AAA (say goodnight, sovereign bond market!) so they will hoard and confiscate properties and cash until valuations are reset to/with a global currency&#8230;</p>
