			March 29, 2013 at 12:52 am</a>		</div>

		<p>Well sure, what&#8217;s good for one thief, is good for another and in this case, all.  The one country who at least &#8220;says&#8221; it is not going to do this will probably be flooded as a safe haven.  But that could be the perfect ruse:  reel &#8216;em in with an &#8216;assurance&#8217; that it won&#8217;t happen here and then let &#8216;em have it en masse.  What is the answer?  Where to hide?  </p>
<p>Like someone else said in another thread&#8212;it won&#8217;t matter whether you have your $$ in the bank or out of the bank. If it is out, they will simply calculate what you &#8220;owe&#8221; as of your balance before starting to withdraw funds and then extort that through taxes, license dues (can&#8217;t drive w/o a D/L and a lot of folks also have prof licenses), etc.  I guess one could start making purchases that did not look to obvious and then turn around and sell those for cash kept anywhere than in a bank.</p>

