		<p>The thread drift toward English-French antagonism is exhibit A for why Canada is screwed. And the elites will be laughing all the way to the bank (literally) given this polarization, just as they do with the duopoly and culture wars in the US. </p>
<p>Quebec has strong movements (but also strong corporations &#8212; think Quebecor), but they are unfortunately so parochial that they don&#8217;t venture out of the province. The rest of Canada suffers from the indoctrination of the global Anglosphere corporate media and has also traditionally been more atomized as a society.  What to do? We need to bridge the gap before it&#8217;s too late.</p>

